The ExtensionLoader here is not only for loading class extensions, but also provides an instance of @Adaptive annotations. The addExtension method is to ensure that the class always provides a default class extension, so that the ExtensionComper will be set to adaptive extension when the ExtensionLoader is loaded. class

You can see the contents of the META-INF/dubbo/inetrnal/org.apache.dubbo.common.compiler.Compiler file in the dubbo-common module.

```
adaptive=org.apache.dubbo.common.compiler.support.AdaptiveCompiler
jdk=org.apache.dubbo.common.compiler.support.JdkCompiler
javassist=org.apache.dubbo.common.compiler.support.JavassistCompiler
```


The place to load the class extension is in the ```getAdaptiveExtensionClass``` method.

```
private Class<?> getAdaptiveExtensionClass() {
   
    //First find all resource files, load all extension classes, but not instantiated
    // In the process of loading the extension class, if you encounter a class with an Adaptive 
    //annotation, the class will be set to the cache cachedAdaptiveClass
    // In this case, the logic to achieve adaptive expansion by the user

    getExtensionClasses();
    if (cachedAdaptiveClass != null) {
        return cachedAdaptiveClass;
    }
   
    return cachedAdaptiveClass = createAdaptiveExtensionClass();
}
```

